Now I understand the bug. The fix adds a check in `__set_cpus_allowed_ptr()` to reject affinity masks that include CPUs outside `task_cpu_possible_mask()`. On a system with N CPUs, setting affinity to include a CPU beyond `cpu_possible_mask` should be rejected.

